body.description: The instinctive action of sucking helps to calm and soothe babies and all parents know there’s nothing more wonderful than a calm, content baby. When mom’s breast isn’t available, our Breast-like pacifier is the next best thing for baby to latch onto in between feeds. Made from super soft silicone, this pacifier feels, moves, flexes and stretches just like skin so there’s less chance of confusion when feeding baby from breast or bottle. The natural feel and flex of this breast-like pacifier, inspired by our award-winning Closer to Nature nipple, provides a reassuring alternative to traditional pacifiers. Perfect if you’re worried that offering your baby a pacifier may disrupt breast or bottle feeding. As the symmetrical silicone baglet is fully reversible, there is no ‘wrong’ side-up so the pacifier will always be placed correctly in your baby’s mouth, even when they put it in their mouth themselves. The Breast-like pacifier shield curves away from baby’s face and offers superior ventilation and extra air flow and prevent the build-up of moisture which helps to protect baby’s delicate skin against irritation. BPA-free and easy to clean - simply pop in a sterilizer, wash by hand or in the dishwasher. We recommend that you replace the pacifier every month and always at the first signs of damage or weakness. We recommend stopping pacifier use when your child is older than 36 months. *as compared to traditional round unvented pacifiers which do not compress as easily.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Natural soothing experience Babies will naturally look to mom for comfort. When mom’s breast isn’t available, the Tommee Tippee Breast-like pacifier is the next best thing for baby to latch onto in between feeds.Taking inspiration from Mother Nature and our award-winning Closer to Nature nipple, this super soft silicone pacifier feels, moves, flexes and stretches just like skin so there’s less chance of confusion when feeding baby from breast or bottle - Perfect if you’re worried that offering your baby a pacifier may disrupt breast or bottle feeding.

Symmetrical design The symmetrical, soft silicone baglet is fully reversible and has no ‘wrong’ side-up so the pacifier will always be placed correctly in your baby’s mouth, even when baby puts the pacifier in their mouth themselves. Kind to baby’s skin Sucking and dribbling can sometimes mean baby’s skin becomes irritated around the mouth. The Tommee Tippee Breast-like pacifier curves away from baby’s face and offers superior ventilation to increase airflow and prevent rashes. Available in different age stages The Breast-like pacifier is suitable for use from birth and is available in two age stages. The 0-6-month size features a smaller nipple and shield for tiny mouths and noses. As your baby grows, you can switch to the 6-18m pacifier which offers the same benefits but with a larger nipple and shield.

Easy to clean Silicone is taste-free and won’t retain any stains or odors. Easy to clean either in a sterilizer, by hand or in the top rack of the dishwasher. BPA-free Always BPA and phthalate-free for your ultimate reassurance. How often should I replace my baby’s pacifier? In the interests of hygiene, we recommend that you change your baby’s pacifier every month. Always check the pacifier before each use and replace at the first signs of damage or weakness. We recommend against prolonged pacifier use over 24 months and stopping pacifier use when your child is older than 36 months.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good, might be a little small for older pre teeth babies
reviews.reviewText: Luckily my fourth baby agrees to taking pacifiers and doesn't seem picky. I am also EBF and she doesn't seem too confused. She always has been a bit lazy at shallow latching but she eventually latches ok. This has been since birth. I hope the paci use isn't making her continue this behavior. She does seem to prefer the round paci rather than an orthodontic one. We were given the Avent soother at the hospital and she likes that. I found these since I need more. They are very soft and flexible. The round body part though is hard plastic (for some reason I thought it would be silky silicone too or something). I think it is unnecesssey to have so many holes around the base of the nipple because sometimes it causes loss of suction if her lips aren't formed exactly just so. Sometimes I hear clacking noise as she sucks, not sure why. At least you can attach a paci strap which Avent does not. I have read silicone quality isn't created equal and cheaper ones can leach heavy metals including lead. I contacted the company and they didn't know but emailed me today with the answer"I have raised the questions you asked and can confirm that our soothers are made of medical grade silicone that does not have any traces of heavy metals or lead"So hope this answers any quality/toxicity concerns someone else other than me have about this.The pacifier does seem a bit small considering this is for babies without teeth and that could be 6-9 months for many! My baby is 4.5 weeks and it seems like it just is ok for her.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars easy to knock out of mouth
reviews.reviewText: My breastfed baby takes these paci’s really well. She likes the nipple shape and feel and we have had absolutely no problem with nipple confusion from using these paci’s. My first child took MAM paci’s and he would get rash’s from moisture build up behind the paci piece around his mouth so I loved the idea of the shape of this paci having no way to have the same issue. But because of the shape of these paci’s my daughter has a hard time keeping them in her mouth. She easily knocks them out while her startle reflex is causing her to swat her arms and when she’s contact napping and moves her head it easily comes out due to how big they are. May work for her better when she’s older but I’m having to order a new type and put these away for now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: All my kids have always preferred this brand over other so when I saw that they had this type of pacifier, I had to try it out.My 14 month old loves these and had no issue getting used to it but my 4 month old needs help keeping it in. I’d say it’s a little bit heavy for a newborn or infant to keep in the first few times but I’m sure my 4 month old will be get used to it.They’re really easy to clean and I like that it’s just one piece, no handles or anything like that, I like the round shape and that the colors are easy to match with different outfits.I know the pacifier is meant to be like a breast if you’re breastfeeding but I found that it doesn’t really make a difference, your baby will either like it or not regardless of being breast or bottle fed.I would definitely recommend giving this pacifier a try though.
